text: San Antonio is an unincorporated community in Buchanan County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== A post office called San Antonio was established in 1855, and remained in operation until 1901. The community's name most likely is a transfer from San Antonio, Texas. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Buchanan County, Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: San Antonio, Missouri
